<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-17T10:27:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-14T12:36:00-05:00" n="166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23996: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Manzanillo</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Walsh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Manzanillo</hi></placeName> (<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1920-05-17T11:27:00-04:00" notBefore="1920-05-14T11:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>].<lb/>[Received May 17, 1920—11:27
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Bandits in charge Manzanillo since 11 a.m. 14th. Destroyer <hi rend="italic">Thornton</hi>, Commander Stirling, arrived 4 p.m.
                                and saved town from violence. Standing by.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Walsh</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>